    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Chemical trial halted on 14 February 2025",
      "Reverted to original emulsion breaker formula",
      "Protocol sampling initiated",
      "Incident reported to BSEE on 20 February 2025"
    ],
    "summary": "On 08 February 2025, a pollution event occurred at the Na Kika platform when a trial emulsion breaker chemical caused frothing/foaming in the produced water treatment system. This led to faulty level readings, liquid carryover in vessels, and discharge of approximately 89 barrels of oil into Gulf of America waters over a 7-day period (08-15 February 2025). The discharge exceeded the daily maximum limit of 42 mg/l. BP personnel did not immediately realize the oil discharge was occurring. Once identified, the chemical trial was stopped and the original emulsion breaker formula was reinstated, successfully ending the sheening.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE Production Operations Support Section should reach out to industry to require additional safeguards to improve detection time when system upsets occur",
      "Operators should have methods in place to detect pollution events besides visual observation, given that produced water outlets are located well below the water surface"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "emulsion breaker chemical trial",
      "produced water system upset",
      "frothing/foaming within production vessels",
      "faulty level readings",
      "liquid carryover",
      "89 barrels oil discharged",
      "outlet 80 feet below water surface",
      "pollution event went unnoticed for 7 days"
    ]
  },
